\begin{frame}
 \frametitle{Conclusions}
 \begin{enumerate}
  \item The phase transition is second order.
  \item Strong anharmonic renormalization in the phonon spectrum.
  \item Strongly anharmonic modes at $\Gamma$ show largest linewidths.
  \item Spectral function displays strongly non-Lorentzian features.
  \item In plane thermal conductivity in good agreement with experiments.
  \item Non-perturbative effects are important for  the thermal conductivity.
  \item SnS high temperature efficient thermoelectric material.
 \end{enumerate}
\end{frame}

